#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:1
msgid "Post-Processing"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:3
msgid ""
"SGLang diffusion supports optional post-processing steps that run after "
"generation to improve temporal smoothness (frame interpolation) or spatial "
"resolution (upscaling). These steps are independent of the diffusion model "
"and can be combined in a single run."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:8
msgid ""
"When both are enabled, **frame interpolation runs first** (increasing the "
"frame count), then **upscaling runs on every frame** (increasing the spatial "
"resolution)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:14
msgid "Frame Interpolation (video only)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:16
msgid ""
"Frame interpolation synthesizes new frames between each pair of consecutive "
"generated frames, producing smoother motion without re-running the diffusion "
"model."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:20
msgid ""
"The `--frame-interpolation-exp` flag controls how many rounds of "
"interpolation to apply: each round inserts one new frame into every gap "
"between adjacent frames, so the output frame count follows the formula:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:24
msgid "**(N − 1) × 2^exp + 1**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:26
msgid ""
"e.g. 5 original frames with `exp=1` → 4 gaps × 1 new frame + 5 originals = "
"**9** frames; with `exp=2` → **17** frames."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:29
#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:76
msgid "CLI Arguments"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Argument"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Description"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "`--enable-frame-interpolation`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid ""
"Enable frame interpolation. Model weights are downloaded automatically on "
"first use."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "`--frame-interpolation-exp {EXP}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid ""
"Interpolation exponent — `1` = 2× temporal resolution, `2` = 4×, etc. "
"(default: `1`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "`--frame-interpolation-scale {SCALE}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid ""
"RIFE inference scale; use `0.5` for high-resolution inputs to save memory "
"(default: `1.0`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "`--frame-interpolation-model-path {PATH}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid ""
"Local directory or HuggingFace repo ID containing RIFE `flownet.pkl` weights "
"(default: `elfgum/RIFE-4.22.lite`, downloaded automatically)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:38
#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:84
msgid "Supported Models"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:40
msgid ""
"Frame interpolation uses the [RIFE](https://github.com/hzwer/Practical-RIFE) "
"(Real-Time Intermediate Flow Estimation) architecture. Only **RIFE 4.22."
"lite** (`IFNet` with 4-scale `IFBlock` backbone) is supported. The network "
"topology is hard-coded, so custom weights provided via `--frame-"
"interpolation-model-path` must be a `flownet.pkl` checkpoint that is "
"compatible with this architecture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:46
msgid ""
"Other RIFE versions (e.g., older `v4.x` variants with different block "
"counts) or entirely different frame interpolation methods (FILM, AMT, etc.) "
"are **not supported**."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Weight"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "HuggingFace Repo"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "RIFE 4.22.lite *(default)*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "[`elfgum/RIFE-4.22.lite`](https://huggingface.co/elfgum/RIFE-4.22.lite)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Lightweight model, downloaded automatically on first use"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:54
msgid "Example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:56
msgid ""
"Generate a 5-frame video and interpolate to 9 frames ((5 − 1) × 2¹ + 1 = 9):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:58
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --model-path Wan-AI/Wan2.2-T2V-A14B-Diffusers \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A dog running through a park\" \\\n"
"  --num-frames 5 \\\n"
"  --enable-frame-interpolation \\\n"
"  --frame-interpolation-exp 1 \\\n"
"  --save-output\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:70
msgid "Upscaling (image and video)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:72
msgid ""
"Upscaling increases the spatial resolution of generated images or video "
"frames using [Real-ESRGAN](https://github.com/xinntao/Real-ESRGAN). The "
"model weights are downloaded automatically on first use and cached for "
"subsequent runs."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "`--enable-upscaling`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Enable post-generation upscaling using Real-ESRGAN."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "`--upscaling-scale {SCALE}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid ""
"Desired upscaling factor (default: `4`). The 4× model is used internally; if "
"a different scale is requested, a bicubic resize is applied after the "
"network output."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "`--upscaling-model-path {PATH}`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid ""
"Local `.pth` file, HuggingFace repo ID, or `repo_id:filename` for Real-"
"ESRGAN weights (default: `ai-forever/Real-ESRGAN` with `RealESRGAN_x4.pth`, "
"downloaded automatically). Use the `repo_id:filename` format to specify a "
"custom weight file from a HuggingFace repo (e.g. `my-org/my-esrgan:weights."
"pth`)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:86
msgid ""
"Upscaling supports two Real-ESRGAN network architectures. The correct "
"architecture is **auto-detected** from the checkpoint keys, so you only need "
"to point `--upscaling-model-path` at a valid `.pth` file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Architecture"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Example Weights"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "**RRDBNet**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "`RealESRGAN_x4plus.pth`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Heavier model with higher quality; best for photos"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "**SRVGGNetCompact**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid ""
"`RealESRGAN_x4.pth` *(default)*, `realesr-animevideov3.pth`, `realesr-"
"general-x4v3.pth`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:0
msgid "Lightweight model; faster inference, good for video"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:95
msgid ""
"The default weight file is [`ai-forever/Real-ESRGAN`](https://huggingface.co/"
"ai-forever/Real-ESRGAN) with `RealESRGAN_x4.pth` (SRVGGNetCompact, 4× native "
"scale)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:99
msgid ""
"Other super-resolution models (e.g., SwinIR, HAT, BSRGAN) are **not "
"supported** — only Real-ESRGAN checkpoints using the two architectures above "
"are compatible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:103
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:105
msgid "Generate a 1024×1024 image and upscale to 4096×4096:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:107
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --model-path black-forest-labs/FLUX.2-dev \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A cat sitting on a windowsill\" \\\n"
"  --output-size 1024x1024 \\\n"
"  --enable-upscaling \\\n"
"  --save-output\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:116
msgid "Generate a video and upscale each frame by 4×:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:118
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --model-path Wan-AI/Wan2.1-T2V-1.3B-Diffusers \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A curious raccoon\" \\\n"
"  --enable-upscaling \\\n"
"  --upscaling-scale 4 \\\n"
"  --save-output\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:129
msgid "Combining Frame Interpolation and Upscaling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:131
msgid ""
"Frame interpolation and upscaling can be combined in a single run. "
"Interpolation is applied first (increasing the frame count), then upscaling "
"is applied to every frame (increasing the spatial resolution)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:135
msgid ""
"Example — generate 5 frames, interpolate to 9 frames, and upscale each frame "
"by 4×:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../diffusion/api/post_processing.md:138
msgid ""
"sglang generate \\\n"
"  --model-path Wan-AI/Wan2.1-T2V-1.3B-Diffusers \\\n"
"  --prompt \"A curious raccoon\" \\\n"
"  --num-frames 5 \\\n"
"  --enable-frame-interpolation \\\n"
"  --frame-interpolation-exp 1 \\\n"
"  --enable-upscaling \\\n"
"  --upscaling-scale 4 \\\n"
"  --save-output\n"
msgstr ""
